Ginóbili was listed as 6 ft 6 in (1.98 m) in shoes, weighed 205 lb (93 kg) and played left-handed. He established himself as a star shooting guard[8] and became known as one of the greatest sixth men in NBA history.[70][71][72] He was a relatively late bloomer, entering the NBA at age 25 in a period when entering the NBA as a teenager was very common.  He was known as a reliable and versatile backcourt player.[5]
